title: Prep Roundup, Oct. 12
text:
Hawks 2-2 at tournament 
The South Hamilton volleyball team went 2-2 at the Hampton-Dumont tournament over the weekend. 
The Hawks went 2-1 in pool play, beating Hampton-Dumont and South Hardin, 2-0, while losing to Charles City, 2-0. In bracket play, South Hamilton lost to Denver, 2-0. 
The Hawks (15-8) play at Greene County tonight. 
CMB struggles at BCLUW Invite 
The Collins-Maxwell-Baxter volleyball team went 0-4 at the BCLUW Invite over the weekend. 
The Raiders dropped matches to North Fayette Valley, North Tama, East Marshall and BCLUW. They won just one set all weekend and lost eight. 
CMB (10-12) plays at North Polk tonight.
